
// Create an [if] statement that checks if the value of the [stream] node inside [.arguments] is true. If so, execute a lambda object that first inserts the nodes referenced by the [@.invoke] expression before the first [fork] child node, and then creates a [fork] node that evaluates the lambda object referenced by [@.invoke].
if
   get-value:x:@.arguments/*/stream
   .lambda
      insert-before:x:./*/fork/0
         get-nodes:x:@.invoke
      fork
         eval:x:@.invoke
